---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Typing Speed Test – WPM Test';
const description = "Free typing speed test: measure your WPM and accuracy in real time with four durations, four text modes, difficulty levels and live feedback.";

const faqs = [
  { q: 'How is WPM calculated?', a: 'WPM uses the standard definition where 1 word = 5 characters. The formula is: WPM = (correctly typed characters ÷ 5) ÷ elapsed minutes. This normalises scores across texts so short and long words count equally. Only correctly typed characters count — errors reduce accuracy but do not inflate WPM.' },
  { q: 'What is a good typing speed?', a: 'The average person types 40–60 WPM. Office workers and frequent computer users typically reach 65–75 WPM. Professional typists and transcriptionists usually exceed 80–90 WPM. Top competitive typists regularly hit 120–150 WPM. Scores above 70 WPM put you ahead of the majority of general computer users.' },
  { q: 'How is accuracy measured?', a: 'Accuracy is (correct characters ÷ total characters typed) × 100. A character you typed wrong and then corrected counts as one error. Aim for 95%+ accuracy before chasing higher WPM — an accurate 65 WPM typist produces less rework than an inaccurate 90 WPM typist who constantly backtracks.' },
  { q: 'What is the difference between the difficulty modes?', a: 'Easy mode uses common everyday words with minimal punctuation. Medium mode introduces varied sentence structures and some punctuation. Hard mode uses complex vocabulary, proper nouns, numbers and extensive punctuation. Technical mode features programming concepts, code snippets and technical jargon. Literature mode uses classic prose with varied sentence lengths and rich vocabulary.' },
  { q: 'Why does correcting errors slow me down?', a: 'Every backspace costs you a keystroke that does not contribute to your WPM score. Experienced typists learn to resist the urge to fix every error mid-sentence and instead focus on forward momentum. For WPM purposes it is often faster to ignore a mistake and keep typing, then review accuracy afterwards.' },
  { q: 'Does this work on mobile devices?', a: 'Yes — tap the text area to open your on-screen keyboard. Mobile typing speeds are typically 30–50% lower than hardware keyboard speeds due to smaller keys and autocorrect interference. Disable autocorrect for the most accurate mobile measurement. For serious WPM benchmarking, use a physical keyboard.' },
  { q: 'How many texts are available?', a: 'There are 24 passages across four categories: 6 General (everyday topics and science), 6 Technical (programming and technology), 6 Literature (classic prose), and 6 Quotes (philosophy and wisdom). The shuffle button picks a random passage from your selected category.' },
];

const faqSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: faqs.map((f) => ({
    '@type': 'Question',
    name: f.q,
    acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a },
  })),
};
const toolSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebApplication',
  name: 'Typing Speed Test',
  applicationCategory: 'UtilityApplication',
  operatingSystem: 'All',
  browserRequirements: 'Requires JavaScript',
  description: 'Free typing speed test — measure WPM and accuracy with 4 text modes and difficulty levels.',
};

const howToSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'HowTo',
  name: 'How to test your typing speed',
  description: 'Measure your typing speed in words per minute (WPM) and your accuracy.',
  step: [
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', position: 1, name: 'Choose a mode', text: 'Select a text mode and difficulty, or a timed test length.' },
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', position: 2, name: 'Start typing', text: 'Begin typing the displayed text exactly as shown — the test starts on your first keystroke.' },
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', position: 3, name: 'Watch it track', text: 'Your words-per-minute and accuracy update live as you type.' },
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', position: 4, name: 'Review results', text: 'Read your final WPM, accuracy and error count, then retry to improve.' },
  ],
};
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} jsonLd={[faqSchema, toolSchema, howToSchema]}>
  <style is:inline>
    :root {
      --primary: #6366f1; --success: #10b981; --error: #ef4444; --warn: #f59e0b;
      --bg: #f8fafc; --card: #ffffff; --text: #1e293b; --muted: #64748b; --border: #e2e8f0;
    }
    .dark body { --bg: #0f172a; --card: #1e293b; --text: #f1f5f9; --muted: #94a3b8; --border: #334155; }

    /* ── Hero (matches SEO Analyzer style) ── */
    .tst-hero {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e1b4b 0%, #312e81 30%, #4c1d95 65%, #2e1065 100%);
      position: relative; overflow: hidden; padding: 40px 20px 44px; text-align: center;
    }
    .tst-hero::before { content:''; position:absolute; top:-80px; right:-80px; width:320px; height:320px; background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(167,139,250,.22) 0%,transparent 70%); pointer-events:none; }
    .tst-hero::after  { content:''; position:absolute; bottom:-60px; left:-60px; width:240px; height:240px; background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(99,102,241,.18) 0%,transparent 70%); pointer-events:none; }
    .tst-badge { display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:5px; margin-bottom:12px; background:rgba(255,255,255,.12); backdrop-filter:blur(8px); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.22); color:#e0e7ff; font-size:.72rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:.08em; padding:4px 14px; border-radius:20px; position:relative; z-index:1; }
    .tst-hero h1 { font-size:clamp(1.5rem,4vw,2.2rem); font-weight:700; color:#fff; margin:0 0 6px; letter-spacing:-.02em; position:relative; z-index:1; }
    .tst-hero p  { font-size:clamp(.85rem,2vw,1rem); color:#c4b5fd; margin:0 0 24px; position:relative; z-index:1; }

    /* ── Hero controls (inside gradient) ── */
    .hero-controls { max-width:680px; margin:0 auto; position:relative; z-index:1; }
    .hero-row { display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; gap:6px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:10px; }
    .hero-sep { width:1px; height:22px; background:rgba(255,255,255,.2); margin:0 2px; }

    /* Duration pills */
    .dur-pill { padding:6px 16px; border-radius:20px; font-size:.82rem; font-weight:700; border:1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,.25); background:rgba(255,255,255,.08); color:rgba(255,255,255,.8); cursor:pointer; transition:all .15s; }
    .dur-pill:hover { background:rgba(255,255,255,.18); border-color:rgba(255,255,255,.45); color:#fff; }
    .dur-pill.active { background:#fff; border-color:#fff; color:#312e81; }

    /* Mode pills */
    .mode-pill { padding:6px 14px; border-radius:20px; font-size:.78rem; font-weight:600; border:1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2); background:rgba(255,255,255,.06); color:rgba(255,255,255,.7); cursor:pointer; transition:all .15s; }
    .mode-pill:hover { background:rgba(255,255,255,.14); color:#fff; }
    .mode-pill.active { background:rgba(99,102,241,.6); border-color:#818cf8; color:#fff; }

    /* Shuffle btn in hero */
    .hero-shuffle { padding:6px 14px; border-radius:20px; font-size:.78rem; font-weight:600; border:1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2); background:rgba(255,255,255,.06); color:rgba(255,255,255,.7); cursor:pointer; transition:all .15s; }
    .hero-shuffle:hover { background:rgba(255,255,255,.14); color:#fff; }

    /* ── Wrap ── */
    .tst-wrap { max-width: 780px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 24px 16px 0; }

    /* ── Stats row ── */
    .stats-row { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr); gap:10px; margin-bottom:16px; }
    .stat-box { background:var(--card); border:1.5px solid var(--border); border-radius:14px; padding:12px 8px; text-align:center; }
    .stat-val { font-size:1.8rem; font-weight:800; color:var(--primary); line-height:1; }
    .stat-lbl { font-size:.68rem; color:var(--muted); margin-top:3px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.06em; }

    /* ── Text display ── */
    .text-display-wrap {
      background:var(--card); border:2px solid var(--border); border-radius:16px;
      padding:22px; cursor:text; position:relative; transition:border-color .2s; min-height:140px;
    }
    .text-display-wrap.active { border-color:var(--primary); }
    .text-display { font-size:1.2rem; line-height:2.1; font-family:'Georgia',serif; user-select:none; overflow-wrap:break-word; }
    @media(max-width:480px) { .text-display { font-size:1rem; } }

    .char.correct { color:var(--success); }
    .char.wrong   { color:var(--error); background:rgba(239,68,68,.1); border-radius:2px; }
    .char.current { border-left:2.5px solid var(--primary); animation:blink .75s step-start infinite; margin-left:-1px; }
    @keyframes blink { 50% { border-color:transparent; } }

    .hidden-input { position:absolute; top:0; left:0; width:1px; height:1px; opacity:0; pointer-events:none; border:none; outline:none; resize:none; }

    /* Idle overlay */
    .idle-overlay { position:absolute; inset:0; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; border-radius:14px; background:rgba(248,250,252,.88); backdrop-filter:blur(2px); flex-direction:column; gap:6px; cursor:pointer; }
    .dark body .idle-overlay { background:rgba(15,23,42,.88); }
    .io-icon { font-size:2.2rem; }
    .io-text { font-size:.95rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--primary); }
    .io-sub  { font-size:.8rem; color:var(--muted); }

    /* Done overlay */
    .done-overlay { position:absolute; inset:0; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; border-radius:14px; background:rgba(248,250,252,.92); backdrop-filter:blur(3px); flex-direction:column; gap:8px; cursor:pointer; }
    .dark body .done-overlay { background:rgba(15,23,42,.92); }
    .do-wpm   { font-size:3.5rem; font-weight:900; color:var(--primary); line-height:1; }
    .do-label { font-size:.75rem; color:var(--muted); text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.08em; }
    .do-sub   { font-size:.9rem; color:var(--muted); }

    /* Progress bar */
    .prog-wrap { height:5px; background:var(--border); border-radius:3px; margin-top:10px; overflow:hidden; }
    .prog-fill { height:100%; background:var(--primary); border-radius:3px; transition:width .2s linear; }

    /* Actions */
    .tst-actions { display:flex; gap:8px; margin-top:14px; flex-wrap:wrap; }
    .btn-primary { padding:9px 22px; border-radius:9px; background:var(--primary); color:#fff; font-size:.9rem; font-weight:600; border:none; cursor:pointer; transition:opacity .15s; }
    .btn-primary:hover { opacity:.88; }
    .btn-outline { padding:9px 22px; border-radius:9px; background:transparent; border:1.5px solid var(--border); color:var(--muted); font-size:.9rem; font-weight:600; cursor:pointer; transition:all .15s; }
    .btn-outline:hover { border-color:var(--primary); color:var(--primary); }

    /* Results panel */
    .results-panel { display:none; background:linear-gradient(135deg,#eef2ff,#f5f3ff); border:2px solid #a5b4fc; border-radius:18px; padding:22px; margin-top:18px; }
    .dark body .results-panel { background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1e1b4b,#2d2060); border-color:#4f46e5; }
    .results-panel.show { display:block; }
    .rp-top { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:14px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:16px; }
    .rp-rating { padding:8px 20px; border-radius:30px; background:var(--primary); color:#fff; font-size:1.05rem; font-weight:800; }
    .rp-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr); gap:10px; }
    @media(min-width:500px) { .rp-grid { grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr); } }
    .rp-item { background:var(--card); border-radius:10px; padding:12px; text-align:center; }
    .rp-item .rv { font-size:1.5rem; font-weight:800; color:var(--primary); }
    .rp-item .rl { font-size:.72rem; color:var(--muted); margin-top:2px; }

    /* History */
    .history-wrap { margin-top:22px; }
    .hist-title { font-size:.8rem; font-weight:700; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.06em; color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:8px; }
    .hist-list { display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:5px; }
    .hist-item { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:10px; padding:8px 12px; background:var(--card); border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:10px; font-size:.86rem; }
    .hist-item.best { border-color:#f59e0b; }
    .hist-item .hr { width:20px; height:20px; border-radius:50%; background:var(--primary); color:#fff; font-size:.65rem; font-weight:700; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; flex-shrink:0; }
    .hist-item.best .hr { background:#f59e0b; }
    .hist-item .hw { font-weight:800; color:var(--primary); min-width:60px; }
    .hist-item .hm { color:var(--muted); }

    /* About section */
    .about-section { max-width:780px; margin:32px auto 0; padding:0 16px; }
    .about-card { background:var(--card); border:1.5px solid var(--border); border-radius:16px; padding:28px; }
    .about-card h2 { font-size:1.3rem; font-weight:800; margin-bottom:16px; }
    .about-card p { font-size:.92rem; line-height:1.8; color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:14px; }
    .about-card p:last-child { margin-bottom:0; }
    .about-card h3 { font-size:1rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--text); margin:20px 0 8px; }

    /* FAQ */
    .faq-section { max-width:780px; margin:28px auto 40px; padding:0 16px; }
    .faq-title { font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:800; margin-bottom:16px; }
    .faq-item { background:var(--card); border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:12px; margin-bottom:10px; }
    .faq-q { padding:14px 16px; font-weight:600; cursor:pointer; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; font-size:.93rem; }
    .faq-q:hover { color:var(--primary); }
    .faq-a { padding:0 16px 14px; font-size:.88rem; color:var(--muted); line-height:1.65; display:none; }
    .faq-item.open .faq-a { display:block; }
    .faq-item.open .faq-arrow { transform:rotate(180deg); }
    .faq-arrow { transition:transform .2s; font-size:.75rem; color:var(--muted); }
  </style>

  <!-- ── Hero with embedded controls ── -->
  <div class="tst-hero">
    <div class="tst-badge">★ FLAGSHIP TOOL</div>
    <h1>⌨️ Typing Speed Test</h1>
    <p>Measure your WPM and accuracy — click the text or start typing to begin</p>

    <div class="hero-controls">
      <!-- Duration row -->
      <div class="hero-row" id="durRow">
        <button class="dur-pill" data-dur="15">15s</button>
        <button class="dur-pill active" data-dur="30">30s</button>
        <button class="dur-pill" data-dur="60">1 min</button>
        <button class="dur-pill" data-dur="120">2 min</button>
        <div class="hero-sep"></div>
        <button class="hero-shuffle" id="heroShuffle">🔀 Shuffle</button>
      </div>
      <!-- Mode row -->
      <div class="hero-row" id="modeRow">
        <button class="mode-pill active" data-mode="general">📝 General</button>
        <button class="mode-pill" data-mode="technical">💻 Technical</button>
        <button class="mode-pill" data-mode="literature">📖 Literature</button>
        <button class="mode-pill" data-mode="quotes">💬 Quotes</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tst-wrap">
    <!-- Live stats -->
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-val" id="liveWpm">–</div><div class="stat-lbl">WPM</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-val" id="liveAcc">–</div><div class="stat-lbl">Accuracy</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-val" id="liveTimer">30</div><div class="stat-lbl">Seconds</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-val" id="liveErrors">0</div><div class="stat-lbl">Errors</div></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Text display -->
    <div class="text-display-wrap" id="displayWrap">
      <div class="text-display" id="textDisplay"></div>
      <textarea class="hidden-input" id="hiddenInput" autocomplete="off" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" spellcheck="false"></textarea>
      <div class="idle-overlay" id="idleOverlay">
        <div class="io-icon">⌨️</div>
        <div class="io-text">Click here or start typing</div>
        <div class="io-sub" id="idleSub">30-second test · General</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Progress bar -->
    <div class="prog-wrap"><div class="prog-fill" id="progFill" style="width:100%"></div></div>

    <!-- Actions -->
    <div class="tst-actions">
      <button class="btn-primary" id="restartBtn">↺ Restart</button>
      <button class="btn-outline" id="newTextBtn">📄 New Text</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Results panel -->
    <div class="results-panel" id="resultsPanel">
      <div class="rp-top">
        <div class="rp-rating" id="rpRating">⚡ Good</div>
        <span style="font-size:.88rem;color:var(--muted)">Test complete!</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rp-grid">
        <div class="rp-item"><div class="rv" id="rpWpm">–</div><div class="rl">WPM</div></div>
        <div class="rp-item"><div class="rv" id="rpAcc">–</div><div class="rl">Accuracy</div></div>
        <div class="rp-item"><div class="rv" id="rpCorrect">–</div><div class="rl">Correct</div></div>
        <div class="rp-item"><div class="rv" id="rpErrors">–</div><div class="rl">Errors</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- History -->
    <div class="history-wrap" id="histWrap" style="display:none;">
      <div class="hist-title">Recent Results</div>
      <div class="hist-list" id="histList"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- About section (700+ words for SEO) -->
  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="about-card">
      <h2>About the Typing Speed Test</h2>
      <p>The ToolNestr Typing Speed Test is a free, browser-based tool that accurately measures how fast and how accurately you type. Whether you are a student looking to improve your keyboarding skills, a professional who spends hours every day writing reports and emails, or a competitive typist chasing a personal best, this test gives you a clear, objective measurement of your typing performance with no sign-up and no software to install.</p>
      <p>Typing speed is measured in WPM, or words per minute. The standard definition used by every professional typing test counts one word as five characters, regardless of actual word length. This normalises scores across different texts — a passage full of short words does not unfairly inflate your WPM compared to a passage of long, complex words. Your WPM score is calculated from only the characters you typed correctly, which means that typing fast but inaccurately gives a lower score than typing at a moderate speed with high accuracy.</p>

      <h3>Four text modes for varied practice</h3>
      <p>The test offers four text mode categories, each with six unique passages. General mode presents everyday topics including science facts, history, nature and culture — ideal for most typists who want a realistic benchmark of day-to-day typing. Technical mode features programming concepts, software engineering explanations, computer science theory and web technology content — perfect for developers and IT professionals who type code-adjacent text all day. Literature mode draws from classic prose and essays, offering longer sentences with richer vocabulary and varied punctuation that challenges advanced typists. Quotes mode presents extended passages from philosophers, scientists, authors and thinkers — inspiring content that also provides a genuine typing challenge.</p>
      <p>You can switch between modes using the buttons in the header before starting a test. Pressing the shuffle button picks a random passage from your current mode, so you never get bored typing the same text repeatedly. The variety across 24 total passages also helps you avoid the memorisation effect where knowing the text in advance artificially inflates your score.</p>

      <h3>Four test durations</h3>
      <p>Choose from 15-second, 30-second, 1-minute and 2-minute test durations. The 15-second test measures your peak burst speed — useful for warm-up or when you just want a quick check. The 30-second test balances speed and a minimal endurance element, making it the most popular choice for everyday benchmarking. The 1-minute test is the traditional typing test standard used by employers and typing certification programmes. The 2-minute test adds a significant endurance component that reveals how well you sustain your peak speed — many typists see their WPM drop noticeably by the second minute as concentration and fatigue set in.</p>

      <h3>Real-time character feedback</h3>
      <p>As you type, each character is instantly colour-coded: green for correct, red for incorrect, and a blinking indigo cursor marks your current position. This immediate visual feedback trains your muscle memory to recognise errors as they happen rather than only at the end. The live stats panel above the text area shows your current WPM, accuracy percentage, remaining time and total error count — all updating every 200 milliseconds so you always know exactly where you stand.</p>

      <h3>Improving your typing speed</h3>
      <p>Research consistently shows that deliberate practice with immediate feedback is the fastest way to improve typing speed. Regular short sessions — even just 10 minutes a day — produce faster results than occasional long practice sessions. Focus on accuracy first: most experts recommend targeting 95% or higher accuracy before trying to increase raw speed. Trying to type faster than your current skill level causes more errors, which slows you down through backspacing and disrupts your rhythm.</p>
      <p>Touch typing — keeping your fingers on the home row keys and using each finger for its designated set of keys — is significantly faster than hunt-and-peck typing for most people once it becomes habit. If you have not learned touch typing, the investment of two to four weeks of deliberate relearning typically pays off within a month. The literature and quotes modes in this test are particularly useful for experienced typists who want to build comfort with complex sentence structures and punctuation.</p>

      <h3>How scores are saved</h3>
      <p>Your last five test results are stored in memory during your browser session and displayed in the Recent Results panel at the bottom of the page. Your personal best WPM is tracked across all tests in the session. Results are not saved between sessions — close the tab and the history is cleared — which maintains complete privacy. No data is ever sent to any server.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2 class="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    {faqs.map((f) => (
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          {f.q}<span class="faq-arrow">▼</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-a">{f.a}</div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
  (function () {
    const TEXTS = {
      general: [
        "The human brain contains approximately 86 billion neurons, each forming thousands of connections with other cells. These intricate networks are responsible for every thought, memory, and emotion we experience. Scientists estimate that the total number of synaptic connections in a single brain exceeds the number of stars in the Milky Way galaxy. Despite decades of research, neuroscientists are still uncovering how these connections give rise to consciousness and creative thought.",
        "Photosynthesis is one of the most fundamental chemical processes on Earth, converting sunlight into the energy that powers nearly all life. Plants absorb carbon dioxide from the air and water from the soil, using light energy to produce glucose and release oxygen as a byproduct. Without photosynthesis, the oxygen in our atmosphere would gradually disappear and most complex life forms would cease to exist. Rainforests alone produce roughly 20 percent of the world's oxygen supply each year.",
        "The printing press, invented by Johannes Gutenberg around 1440, is widely regarded as one of the most transformative inventions in human history. Before the printing press, books were laboriously copied by hand, making them rare and extraordinarily expensive. Within 50 years of the press's invention, over 20 million books had been printed across Europe, democratising knowledge and laying the groundwork for the Renaissance, the Reformation, and the Scientific Revolution. Information had never spread so quickly before.",
        "Ocean currents act as a global conveyor belt, distributing heat from the equator toward the poles and regulating the climate of entire continents. The Gulf Stream, for example, keeps Western Europe significantly warmer than it would otherwise be at the same latitude. Climate scientists warn that global warming could weaken or disrupt these currents, potentially causing rapid and dramatic climate shifts in affected regions. Understanding ocean circulation is therefore critical to modelling future climate scenarios accurately.",
        "The Great Wall of China stretches over 13,000 miles across northern China and was built over many centuries by successive dynasties. Contrary to popular belief, it is not visible from space with the naked eye — astronauts have confirmed this myth to be false. The wall served primarily as a military fortification and transportation corridor rather than an impenetrable barrier. It employed hundreds of thousands of workers, including soldiers, peasants, and prisoners, many of whom died during construction and were buried within the wall itself.",
        "Sleep is not merely a passive state of rest but an active biological process essential for physical and mental health. During deep sleep, the brain clears toxic waste products that accumulate during waking hours, including proteins linked to Alzheimer's disease. Memory consolidation also occurs during sleep, with the hippocampus replaying experiences from the day and transferring them into long-term storage. Adults who consistently sleep fewer than seven hours per night show measurable declines in cognitive performance, immune function, and emotional regulation.",
      ],
      technical: [
        "Version control systems like Git allow developers to track changes to their codebase over time, collaborate with teammates, and safely experiment with new features without breaking existing functionality. Every change is recorded with a commit message, author name, and timestamp, creating a full audit trail of the project's history. Branching allows multiple developers to work on different features simultaneously, and merging integrates those changes back into the main codebase. Understanding Git is considered a fundamental skill for any professional software developer today.",
        "RESTful APIs use HTTP methods to enable communication between client applications and servers. GET requests retrieve resources, POST requests create new ones, PUT and PATCH update existing records, and DELETE removes them. Each resource is identified by a unique URL called an endpoint, and responses typically return data in JSON format. Proper REST design includes statelessness, meaning the server does not store client session information between requests, which improves scalability and allows load balancers to route requests to any available server.",
        "The browser's rendering pipeline begins when the HTML parser converts markup into a Document Object Model tree. CSS is then parsed into a CSS Object Model, and the two trees are combined into a render tree containing only the visible elements. The layout stage calculates the exact position and size of every element on the page, and the paint stage converts those layout instructions into pixels. Modern browsers use GPU-accelerated compositing to achieve smooth 60-frames-per-second animations without blocking the main thread.",
        "Database indexing dramatically speeds up query performance by creating a separate data structure that allows the database engine to locate rows without scanning the entire table. A B-tree index, the most common type, stores values in a sorted structure that enables lookups in O(log n) time instead of O(n). However, indexes consume disk space and slow down write operations because they must be updated on every insert, update, and delete. Experienced database administrators carefully choose which columns to index based on the actual query patterns of the application.",
        "Containerisation with Docker packages an application and all its dependencies into a lightweight, portable image that runs consistently across different environments. Unlike virtual machines, containers share the host operating system kernel, making them far more resource-efficient. Docker Compose orchestrates multi-container applications, allowing developers to define the entire stack — including databases, caches, and message queues — in a single configuration file. In production, Kubernetes extends this further by automating container deployment, scaling, and self-healing across clusters of machines.",
        "WebAssembly, abbreviated as Wasm, is a low-level binary instruction format that runs in modern browsers at near-native speed. It allows code written in languages like C, C++, Rust, and Go to be compiled and executed in the browser alongside JavaScript. This opens the door to computationally intensive web applications such as video editors, game engines, image processors, and scientific simulations that were previously only possible in native desktop applications. WebAssembly does not replace JavaScript but complements it, handling the heavy computation while JavaScript manages the DOM and user interface.",
